}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 Fairfax County Police To Discuss Active Violence Incidents - }{\plain \fs24 \f8 Given the on-going incidents of church targeted \softline
violence, the BOSL asked the Fairfax County Police Department to come and speak on June 2nd, between services \softline
(9:45am) about active violence incidents.  A member from the Fairfax County Police Department will be at Living \softline
Savior to discuss Active Violence Incidents and how churches can better protect themselves in the unfortunate \softline
and unlikely incidence of an active shooter at church.  Case studies will be presented and best approaches to \softline
dealing with situations like these will be shared.   All congregation members are encouraged to attend this \softline
important presentation and if you have any questions, please contact Jonathan Loesch.  \par
